hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: How many more years do you have to go? cetromed.com Trussed up high in a paragliding harness, on a still and silent blue sky day, I am far from being alone. Freddy is my guide. He swoops up, then dives left, darts below, then swoops right, like a military escort playing truant. “Come on, Freddy!” I yell at him. He is always a good 50m away, and tantalisingly out of reach. It is exhilarating – and maddening. My arm is outstretched, covered with a stiff leather gauntlet and a bit of dead mouse, as he glides in a wide circle behind me. He is the Harris hawk that got away.
